    host_own_geo: "Currently only in Munich and Berlin. Interested in Stockholm, Milan, Hamburg, London or Madrid? <a href=\"mailto:franziska.wittleder@gmail.com\" style=\"color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);text-decoration:underline;\">Write to us.</a>",
    host_own_btn: "Host your own evening →",
    host_own_fine: "You pick the date · enter your name · receive a ready-to-share link · from min. 12 people · €78 incl. catering",
    faq_label: "FAQ",
    faq_h2: "Frequently asked questions",
    faq_q1: "Who hosts the Salon?",
    faq_a1: "Salon AI is founded and led by <strong>Franziska Wittleder</strong>. 15+ years in AI research, engineering and product leadership across scale-ups and big tech (Amazon, Writer and SoundCloud) — across the US and EU. Creative direction by Tatjana Mallinckrodt (Head of PR &amp; Brand Strategy at Gestalten / teNeues) — because tech doesn't have to be sterile. The evening has a gently immersive note: we weave nature into the tech, from the table dressing on out. 🌿",
    faq_q2: "How does this differ from other AI evenings in Munich?",
    faq_a2: "You build, not just watch — every person builds their own AI assistant. Small circle in salon format with dinner and drinks, no seminar-room feel. And the agent you build is applied directly to a real EU task: identifying MEPs, filing consultation responses, commenting on regulations.",
    faq_q3: "What came out of the March Salon?",
    faq_a3: "15 people developed the website \"Europe 2041\" together in a single evening — built AI assistants, gathered EU ideas, published them. The result: <a href=\"/march-event/\" style=\"color:var(--sky-deep)\">www.salon-ai.eu/march-event</a>",
    faq_q4: "What is the Salon AI Dinner Munich?",
    faq_a4: "An AI evening in salon format. In a single evening you build your own AI assistant — and apply it directly to an EU task. Next event: 28 May 2026, Luitpoldblock Munich, €78 (dinner and drinks included). No lecture, no watching — you build yourself.",
    faq_q5: "Do I need prior knowledge?",
    faq_a5: "No. No coding, no tech background, no prior AI experience required. The evening is for everyone — beginners or daily users alike. Experts accompany the entire evening, one-on-one.",
    faq_q6: "What do I need to bring?",
    faq_a6: "A laptop. Nothing else. We recommend a Pro account on an AI tool of your choice (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini or Mistral) — if you don't have one, we'll set it up on site. Concrete details come with the reservation confirmation.",
    faq_q7: "Is there food and drink?",
    faq_a7: "Yes. Modern Middle Eastern Cuisine and drinks are fully included in the €78 ticket price. It's a real dinner — no seminar room with biscuits.",
    faq_q8: "What does \"AI for Europe\" actually mean?",
    faq_a8: "In the second half you use your finished agent for a real EU task. Documented examples: 23 MEPs of an EU committee identified and individually contacted in 20 minutes. Cross-border healthcare claim filed (EU right with cost reimbursement). EU consultation response on AI regulation written. You leave with a concrete result.",
    faq_q9: "Can I organise the evening with my own group?",
    faq_a9: "Yes — actively encouraged. From 12 to 20 people we come to you. Same format, your own EU group brief. <a href=\"/host.html\" style=\"color:var(--sky-deep);font-weight:600;\">Set up your evening here →</a> or: franziska.wittleder@gmail.com",
    faq_q10: "What about cancellations?",
    faq_a10: "If you cancel up to 3 days before the dinner we keep 50% of the ticket price, after that the full amount. You can transfer the ticket to another person at any time — just pass on the name and contact, no problem. Questions: franziska.wittleder@gmail.com",
